From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 10:46:49 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native particles_copy
 in-frame fill-instances replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 + 0041 + 0042 (the branch-HEAD gpu_culling tail
plus the tonemap, ssao_blur and taa_resolve rd_native slices). This is the
fourth Route B REAL replacement pass and the FIRST buffer-path rd_native slice:
Route B drives the Rurix particles_copy kernel as a first-class in-frame
RenderingDevice compute dispatch for the COPY_MODE_FILL_INSTANCES 3D
fill-instances subset, instead of the out-of-frame rxgd shim bridge, and when it
records the native Godot fill-instances dispatch is genuinely skipped (one fewer
native dispatch; no scaffold clear, unlike patch 0022).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_particles_copy_rd_native(int64_t compute_list, RID src_particles,
  RID dst_instances, uint32_t total_particles, const uint8_t *push_constants,
  uint32_t push_constant_bytes). It takes the Godot ComputeListID of the
  ALREADY-OPEN particles_set_view_axis fill-instances compute list (that function
  opens one list around the copy dispatch, so rd_native must NOT begin/end its
  own) plus the two Godot structured-buffer RID handles (not native
  ID3D12Resource* handles like the shim-path try_record_particles_copy) so the
  module can build an RD uniform set and record one dispatch. Base returns false.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings,
  independent of the four existing particles_copy shim settings (untouched):
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/particles_copy/backend (int, default 0;
  0=disabled / 1=shim / 2=rd_native) and
  rendering/rurix_accel/passes/particles_copy/rd_container_path (string, default
  ""). Defaults keep the RD-native path disabled.
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_particles_copy_rd_native
  override. Lazily builds the compute pipeline once (FileAccess reads the Rurix
  container -> shader_create_from_bytecode -> compute_pipeline_create, latching
  rd_native_particles_copy_load_failed on any failure so it is not retried per
  frame), binds t0=src_particles and u0=dst_instances via UniformSetCacheRD both
  as UNIFORM_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER (the buffer probe proved RAW == structured
  equivalence at zero tolerance), passes the 128-byte CopyPushConstant b0 mirror
  verbatim, and records a total-particles dispatch onto the caller's compute list
  (compute_list_dispatch_threads divides by the container's local size). No
  submit()/sync() (a local-RD-only concept). The one-shot
  RXGD_RD_NATIVE_PARTICLES_COPY active marker is emitted via print_verbose when
  the pipeline is first built (not per-frame). Unlike the texture passes,
  particles_copy carries no i64 push-constant fields and does no usage-bits
  preflight (buffers have no texture_get_format).
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/storage_rd/particles_storage.cpp
  particles_set_view_axis: in the fill-instances leg, backend == 2 runs the
  rd_native gate BEFORE the shim gate, and ONLY for the plain 3D fill-instances
  subset (!do_sort AND copy_mode_2d == 0); a successful record skips both the shim
  gate and the native fill-instances dispatch. backend != 2 leaves the
  pre-existing shim/native chain byte-for-byte unchanged.

Fail-closed everywhere: with the default backend == 0 (and empty container path),
rd_native is never engaged and the native Godot particles copy renders. The
kernel covers only the ALIGN_DISABLED/ALIGN_Z_BILLBOARD 3D fill-instances subset
(no 2D, sort/VIEW_DEPTH, lifetime reindex, trail, or userdata), so only that
subset routes through rd_native and the rest stay native. RXGD_ABI_VERSION is
unchanged (this path does not touch the C ABI struct layout and sets no
RxGdCaps.flags bit; rd_native is bridge-independent). No performance claim is
made.
